  "final_analysis": "The core medical principle in the treatment of subarachnoid hemorrhage involves the prevention of cerebral vasospasm, a potentially life-threatening complication. Nimodipine, a calcium channel blocker, is specifically indicated for this purpose due to its preferential effect on cerebral arteries, which helps in reducing the incidence of cerebral vasospasm following a subarachnoid hemorrhage. Other calcium channel blockers like Amlodipine, Diltiazem, and Verapamil, although effective in other cardiovascular conditions, do not have the same specificity or evidence supporting their use in the prevention of cerebral vasospasm associated with subarachnoid hemorrhage. Therefore, based on medical consensus and supported evidence, Nimodipine is the most appropriate and effective choice for this indication.",
